fields.name: Bassoon
fields.description: The bassoon is a woodwind instrument in the double reed family that plays music written in the bass and tenor clefs, and occasionally the treble. This piece is ideal for beginners and intermediate players

fields.name: Bongos
fields.description: Bongos are an Afro-Cuban percussion instrument consisting of a pair of small open bottomed drums of different sizes. In Spanish the larger drum is called the hembra and the smaller the macho. Are you macho enough to try these fellas out

fields.name: Guitar Cable
fields.description: Whether for studio or a live performance this guitar cable will not let you down. We've got a wide selection of lengths and patches.

fields.name: Cello
fields.description: The cello or violoncello is a bowed string instrument of the violin family. Its four strings are usually tuned in perfect fifths: from low to high, C₂, G₂, D₃ and A₃. With our cello your ears will be tuned in perfect harmony.

fields.name: Clarinet
fields.description: The clarinet is a family of woodwind instruments. It has a single-reed mouthpiece, a straight, cylindrical tube with an almost cylindrical bore, and a flared bell. A person who plays a clarinet is called a clarinetist. Make yourself a one and order from our shop today!

fields.name: Conga
fields.description: The conga, also known as tumbadora, is a tall, narrow, single-headed drum from Cuba. It's not a cigar but hey, it's a healthy version of fun.

fields.name: Double Bass
fields.description: The double bass, also known simply as the bass (or by other names), is the largest and lowest-pitched bowed (or plucked) string instrument in the modern symphony orchestra. Definitely a largest pal in our shop.

fields.name: Djembe
fields.description: According to the Bambara people in Mali, the name of the djembe comes from the saying Anke djé, anke bé which translates to everyone gather together in peace and defines the drum's purpose. Enough said.

fields.name: Drum Set
fields.description: Are you ready to shake the hall with this loud beast? Crashes, Hi Hats, Snare, Toms and bass drum all included to make the rumble that's not humble.

fields.name: Flugelhorn
fields.description: It resembles a trumpet, but it's not. Nickel silver outer slides, Third valve slide trigger, 3 Water keys, Lacquer finish. Just about everything you need from a Flugelhorn.

fields.name: Flute
fields.description: Unlike other woodwind instruments with reeds, a flute is an aerophone or reedless wind instrument that produces its sound from the flow of air across an opening. Nicest sounding air flow we have ever heard. Just try it for yourself if you don't believe us.

fields.name: French Horn
fields.description: A musician who plays a horn is known as a horn player or hornist. This instrument is intended for a student. So in this case player would be called a student hornist? No? Ok...

fields.description: The trombone is another member of the brass musical family. As with all brass instruments, sound is produced when the player's vibrating lips (embouchure) cause the air column inside the instrument to vibrate, just like your body will vibrate out of joy while playing it.

fields.name: Trumpet

fields.name: Tuba

fields.name: Ukulele
